# Banned Speeches

Standards to ensure optimal display on all mail clients (Outlook, Gmail, Apple Mail…).

---

## Standard formats

| Format                                             | Dimensions (L × H)                    | Typical location                              |
| :------------------------------------------------- | :------------------------------------------------------- | :-------------------------------------------- |
| **Banned Banner** (Leaderboard) | **600 × 150 px** _(sometimes 640 px)_ | Header or Email Heart — Most Impactful Format |
| **Pave** (Rectangle)            | **300 × 250 px**                                         | Late column or email footer — compact format  |

---

## Technical Constraints

| Crite                 | Specification                                                                      |
| :-------------------- | :--------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **File type**         | JPG, PNG or GIF                                                                    |
| **Colorimetric mode** | [currency symbol] RGB          |
| **Maximum Weight**    | 150 KB — recommended < **80 KB** for fast mobile charging |

:::warning GIF animated — first frame regeneration
animated GIFs are accepted, but **Outlook (desktop versions) only displays the first image**.

→ Main information and Call-to-Action must not appear on the **first frame**.
:::

---

## Best Design Practices

:::tip White background: add border
If your banner has a white background, it may melt into the email background, and become invisible.

Add a **grey border of 1 px** (`#cccccccc`) all around your design to define it correctly.
:::

:::tip Mobile readability
On mobile, a 600 px banner is reduced to ~350 px wide. Avoid too thin or too small fonts — **recommended minimum size: 16 px**.
:::
